    <body>
      <head>Tomáš [Thomas; Tommy] Kornfeld</head>

      <div>
        <p>Son of <ref cRef="entity-000468">Felix Kornfeld</ref>, grandson of <ref
            cRef="entity-000466">Emil Kornfeld</ref> and Jenny Kornfeld (later <ref
            cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref>) of <ref cRef="entity-002248">Aussig</ref>
          (Bohemia/Czechoslovakia).</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <head>Correspondence and Photograph</head>

        <p>Correspondence between Heribert Esser and Tomáš Kornfeld survives in photocopy as <ref
            type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-71-10a_1">OJ 71/10a, [1]</ref> and <ref
            type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-71-21a_1">OJ 71/21a, [1]</ref>-<ref type="correspondence"
            cRef="OJ-71-21a_2">[2]</ref> (1988). A photograph of Tomáš, inscribed "Tommy Kornfeld,
          born August 7, 1932, taken on August 7, 1939" survives as OJ 72/9, the photographer being
          Karl Engel, Aussig (originally enclosed with <ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-14-7_1"
            >OJ 14/7, [1]</ref>, letter from Felix Kornfeld to Jeanette Schenker, August 23,
          1939).</p>
      </div>
    </body>

